SIMPLE: extinct
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extinct
<hw>Ex*tinct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>extinctus</ets>, <ets>exstinctus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>extinguere</ets>, <ets>exstinguere</ets>. See
<er>Extinguish</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Extinguished; put out;
quenched; <as>as, a fire, a light, or a lamp, is <ex>extinct</ex>; an
<ex>extinct</ex> volcano.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Light, the prime work of God, to me is <qex>extinct</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without a survivor; without force; dead; <as>as, a
family becomes <ex>extinct</ex>; an <ex>extinct</ex> feud or
law.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>Once existing as a
species but now having no living members; -- used of species of living
organisms, especially of animals and plants; <as>as, dinosaurs are now
<ex>extinct</ex>; the dodo bird is <ex>extinct</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extinct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Extinct
<hw>Ex*tinct"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to be extinct.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extinction</ent>⟦br⟧
